    "body": "## Steps to reproduce\r\n1. Open a webpage with links/linked images (i.e. Google images, https://en.wikipedia.org/).\r\n2. From Portrait mode, long tap on a link/linked image.\r\n3. Observe the URL of the page displayed at the top of the context menu.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\nThe URL displayed at the top of the context menu should be static.\r\n### Actual behavior\r\nWhen the context menu is invoked from the Portrait mode, the URL displayed at the top changes its position.\r\n### Device information\r\n\r\n* Android device: Xiaomi Redmi Note 8T (Android 9).\r\n* Focus version: RC 98.3.0, Nightly 100.0a1.\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/89388888/159723678-7855d64e-be22-4710-be2c-1cfa8c0fa74f.mp4\r\n\r\nOn Focus Nightly 100.0a1 from 03/23, the issue is slightly different: When the context menu is invoked from the Portrait mode, the space between the URL's position and the top edge of the context menu is bigger. Changing the orientation to Landscape, then back to Portrait mode will reduce the initial space between the URL's position and the top edge of the context menu.\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/89388888/159723729-2e275015-bd2a-45bf-82e0-e18d03964cc4.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n",
